GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Analogy> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_Analogy> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Analogy> ;
    narr:childCount "31"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "b5a7129694e084f38111d1bc15a52a4e4d650909" ;
    narr:narration """The rhetorical architecture of aswritten relies on [familiar technical and cultural analogies](narr:StyleObs_2) to bridge the gap between AI capabilities and human workflows. This strategy consistently follows a pattern of [citing the known, then asserting the upgrade](narr:StyleObs_LeanStartupAnalogy). Engineering-led audiences are frequently engaged through [software development metaphors](narr:StyleObs_Analogy_1), most notably the [PR-with-unit-tests framework](narr:StyleObs_CustomerCTOPRMetaphor_Analogy), which gained significant weight after being independently deployed by a skeptical enterprise CTO. Other recurring frames include [pop-culture skill transfer](narr:StyleObs_KungFu), [academic peer-review accountability](narr:StyleObs_TamarackReview_PeerReviewAnalogy), and [opinionated product-identity contrasts](narr:StyleObs_OpinionatedWorkflow). Recent developments have integrated [design-token parallels](narr:StyleObs_DesignCollaboratorTokensAnalogy) and [historical technology pairings](narr:StyleObs_CompanionAnalogy) to argue for market timing. While these analogies serve as essential translation layers, they are [occasionally qualified by their own limitations](narr:Narrative_CarfaxSubstackAnalogy), particularly when the complexity of aswritten's synthesis exceeds the scope of the original metaphor.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_CarfaxSubstackAnalogy> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_MemoryIngestionAsCodeReview> ;
